                    <span>This is really a five star book. However it is generic and only dated to the extent that there is more information now. The concepts and methoods are still sound<BR>Want to know about SAR?<BR>When you time an application do you want to know what the user-state CPU time and systemstate CPU time means?<BR>Many of the pertinent questions and answers to System Performance Tuning are in this book. The chapters are:<P>· Introduction to System Performance<BR>· Monitoring System Activity<BR>· Managing the Workload<BR>· Memory Performance<BR>· Disk Performance Issues<BR>· Network Performance<BR>· Terminal Performance<BR>· Kernel Configuration<BR>· Appendix A Real-time Processes<BR>· Appendix B A Performance Tuning Strategy<P>This book has helped point to the pertinent manuals on several flavors of UNIX.</span>
                  
              
